      • appointmentSoonAlert

        public static void appointmentSoonAlert​(Appointment appointment)
        Displays a dialogue box showing the user the next appointment that starts within 15 minutes of user login. If there is no appointment within 15 minutes, it displays that information to the user instead.
        Parameters:
        appointment - that begins within 15 minutes of user login

      • fieldCheckAppointment

        public static boolean fieldCheckAppointment​(java.lang.String title,
                                            java.lang.String description,
                                            java.lang.String location,
                                            java.lang.String type,
                                            java.time.ZonedDateTime startTimeZDT,
                                            java.time.ZonedDateTime endTimeZDT,
                                            int customerID,
                                            int userID,
                                            int contactID)
        Displays an alert box if an appointment record has an invalid input by checking if: the title, description, location, or type fields are left null; the end time is before the start time; the customerID, userID or ContactID do not have existing associated records.
        Parameters:
        title - name of the appointment
        description - description of the appointment
        location - of the appointment
        type - of the appointment
        startTimeZDT - start time of the appointment
        endTimeZDT - end time of the appointment
        customerID - associated customer ID
        userID - associated user ID
        contactID - associated contact ID
        Returns:
        true if the format is valid, false if it is not

      • NoScheduleConflict

        public static boolean NoScheduleConflict​(int appointmentId,
                                         java.time.ZonedDateTime startTimeZDT,
                                         java.time.ZonedDateTime endTimeZDT,
                                         int customerID)
        There are two Lambda expressions in this method used in together. First the associated list is filtered by the given conditions, then loops through the list again and returns true if there are no Appointments that match the given described in the 'Predicate<> condition' expressing.
        Parameters:
        appointmentId - ID of the appointment. Used to exclude this appointment from 'condition' predicate when checking for scheduled conflicts in cases of updating an appointment rather than creating a new one.
        startTimeZDT - start time of the appointment to be made
        endTimeZDT - end time of the appointment to be made
        customerID - id of the customers appointment to be scheduled
        Returns:
        true if the appointment does not conflict with an existing appointments start and end time
